  "prompt": "How can I retrieve deleted messages on messenger?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to potentially retrieve deleted Messenger messages:\n\n1. Check Facebook Messenger Archive\n- Open Messenger\n- Click on the person's conversation\n- Select \"See All\" in the info section\n- Look in the archived messages\n\n2. Check Message Requests\n- Open Messenger\n- Click on Message Requests\n- Sometimes deleted messages appear here\n\n3. Recovery on Mobile/Desktop\n- Facebook occasionally keeps temporary backups\n- Check recent conversation history\n\n4. Facebook Data Download\n- Go to Facebook Settings\n- Select \"Download a copy of your Facebook data\"\n- Choose \"Messages\" option\n- This might include previously deleted messages\n\n5. Third-Party Recovery Tools\n- Some apps claim to recover deleted messages\n- Be cautious and verify their legitimacy\n- Examples: Dr. Fone, EaseUS MobiSaver\n\n6. Contact Facebook Support\n- If messages are critically important\n- Facebook support might help recover them\n\nImportant Limitations:\n- Not all deleted messages can be retrieved\n- Success depends on how/when messages were deleted\n- Some methods might not work in all scenarios\n\nRecommendation: Always back up important conversations regularly to prevent permanent loss.",
